relevant_findings.cutaneous: brown, infiltrative lesions (5 to 10 mm in diameter) over the trunk and back, consistent with mastocytosis
relevant_findings.mass: mass on the back of the neck, consistent with a lipoma
relevant_findings.mandibular: enlargement of the lingual mandible anteriorly and on the right with no dental dysplasia or dysplasia of the palate or jaw bone
relevant_findings.scarring: surgical scarring and fibrosis over the mandible and neck on the right side
